This paper deals with the problem of matrix completion, which is a common topic in machine learning and optimization. The use of spectral techniques and manifold optimization suggests that this paper is likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the applications mentioned in the abstract, such as collaborative filtering and structure-from-motion, suggest that this paper could also be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the use of optimization techniques suggests that this paper could also be categorized under cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
